SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 976
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR BLACK.
5436S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal section 105.465, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof one new section relating to candidate
committees.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Section 105.465, RSMo, is repealed and one new
2 section enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as section 105.465,
3 to read as follows:
1 105.465. 1. Any person who registers as a lobbyist
2 shall dissolve his or her candidate committee. In the
3 course of dissolving such committee, such person shall not
4 disburse moneys from such committee, except for the purpose
5 of:
6 (1) Returning a contribution made to the candidate
7 committee to the entity responsible for making the
8 contribution to the committee;
9 (2) Donating moneys to a nonprofit entity qualified as
10 exempt from federal taxation under Section 501(c)(3) of the
11 Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended; or
12 (3) Transferring moneys to a political party committee.
13 2. Notwithstanding subsection 1 of this section to the
14 contrary, no person who registers as a lobbyist shall be
15 prohibited from maintaining a candidate committee designated
16 to seek election to a county, municipal, or school board
17 office, provided such person is not registered to lobby the

SB 976 2
18 county, municipality, or school district for which that
19 person's candidate committee is designated to seek office.
20 A candidate committee maintained under this subsection shall
21 make no expenditures or disbursements except to support the
22 candidacy of the person maintaining the committee or for any
23 purpose authorized by subdivisions (1) to (3) of subsection
24 1 of this section.
25 3. For purposes of this section, the term "lobbyist"
26 shall have the same meaning given to such term under section
27 105.470, and the terms "committee", "candidate committee",
28 "contribution", "office", "public office", and "political
29 party committee" shall have the same meanings given to such
30 terms under section 130.011.
